.TH man 8 "18 October 2020" "1.0" "build_kernel man page"
.SH NAME
build_kernel \- build and compile linux kernel 
.SH SYNOPSIS
build_kernel [./build_kernel]
.SH DESCRIPTION
build_kernel is a shell script that builds and compiles a modified linux kernel. It starts off by installing prerequisite packages, git clones a kernel source code and s3656006 assignment repository. It then generates a kernel configuration, modifies and compiles it. Copies necessary files and reboots the device to load new kernel.
.SH OPTIONS
The build_kernel does not take any options. However, you can './build kernel &' to run in background.
.SH SEE ALSO
get_temp 
.SH BUGS
No known bugs.
.SH AUTHOR
Milos Mladenovic (s3656006@student.rmit.edu.au)
